Basics of CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)
1. Introduction to CSS
CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) ek styling language hai jo HTML elements ko design karne ke liye use hoti hai.

CSS kyun important hai?
Website ko attractive banata hai.

Colors, fonts, spacing aur layout control karta hai.

Responsive design banane mein help karta hai.

HTML aur design ko alag rakhta hai.

Example
HTML




<p>Hello World</p>
CSS

p{
    color: blue;
    font-size: 20px;
}
2. Understanding CSS Syntax
Syntax Structure
CSS

selector {
    property: value;
}
Example
CSS

h1{
    color: red;
    font-size: 30px;
}
h1 → Selector

color → Property

red → Value

3. Selectors in CSS
Selectors HTML elements ko select karte hain styling ke liye.

Element Selector
CSS

p{
    color: blue;
}
Sabhi <p> tags par apply hoga.

Class Selector
CSS

.myClass{
    color: green;
}
HTML




<p class="myClass">Hello</p>
ID Selector
CSS

#myId{
    color: red;
}
HTML




<p id="myId">Hello</p>
4. Comments in CSS
Comments browser ignore karta hai.

Single Line Comment
CSS

/* This is a comment */
Example
CSS

/* Heading Styling */
h1{
    color: blue;
}
5. Adding CSS to HTML
Inline CSS
HTML tag ke andar style attribute use karte hain.

HTML




<p style="color:red;">Hello</p>
Advantages
Quick styling

Disadvantages
Reusable nahi hoti

Internal CSS
HTML file ke <head> section mein likhte hain.

HTML




<head>
<style>
p{
    color: blue;
}
</style>
</head>
External CSS
Alag .css file banate hain.

HTML
HTML




<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
style.css
CSS

p{
    color: green;
}
Advantages
Reusable

Professional method

6. Difference Between Class, ID and Element Selectors
Selector	Symbol	Use
Element	tag name	Sabhi same tags ko style karne ke liye
Class	.	Multiple elements par same style lagane ke liye
ID	#	Unique element ko style karne ke liye

Example
HTML




<h1 id="heading">Title</h1>

<p class="text">Paragraph 1</p>
<p class="text">Paragraph 2</p>
CSS

#heading{
    color:red;
}

.text{
    color:blue;
}
7. Understanding Precedence of Selectors
Agar ek hi element par multiple styles apply ho rahi hain to priority ka rule follow hota hai.

Priority Order

Inline CSS
   ↓
ID Selector
   ↓
Class Selector
   ↓
Element Selector
Example
HTML




<p id="demo" class="text" style="color:red;">
Hello
</p>
CSS

p{
    color: blue;
}

.text{
    color: green;
}

#demo{
    color: orange;
}
Output
Text Red hoga kyunki Inline CSS ki priority sabse zyada hoti hai.

8. Text Styling Properties in CSS
1. font-family
Text ka font change karta hai.

CSS

p{
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}
2. font-style
Text ko italic ya normal banata hai.

CSS

p{
    font-style: italic;
}
Values:

normal

italic

oblique

3. font-weight
Text ki thickness control karta hai.

CSS

p{
    font-weight: bold;
}
Values:

normal (400)

bold (700)

100 to 900

4. line-height
Lines ke beech spacing set karta hai.

CSS

p{
    line-height: 30px;
}
5. text-decoration
Text decoration add/remove karta hai.

CSS

p{
    text-decoration: underline;
}
Values:

underline

overline

line-through

none

6. text-align
Text alignment set karta hai.

CSS

p{
    text-align: center;
}
Values:

left

center

right

justify

7. text-transform
Text ke letters ka format change karta hai.

CSS

p{
    text-transform: uppercase;
}
Values:

uppercase

lowercase

capitalize

8. letter-spacing
Letters ke beech distance set karta hai.

CSS

p{
    letter-spacing: 3px;
}
9. word-spacing
Words ke beech distance set karta hai.

CSS

p{
    word-spacing: 10px;
}
10. text-shadow
Text ke piche shadow add karta hai.

CSS

h1{
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 5px gray;
}
Format
CSS

text-shadow: horizontal vertical blur color;
Example
CSS

h1{
    text-shadow: 3px 3px 4px red;
}
Quick Revision
Property	Purpose
font-family	Font change
font-style	Italic/Normal
font-weight	Boldness
line-height	Line spacing
text-decoration	Underline etc.
text-align	Alignment
text-transform	Uppercase/Lowercase
letter-spacing	Letter gap
word-spacing	Word gap
text-shadow	Text shadow